  "description": {
    "en-US": "Travel phrases for Thailand with audio, built around BTS and MRT rides, Grab pickups, hotel check-ins, street-food ordering, and emergency help.",
    "zh-CN": "泰国旅行短语卡，围绕 BTS 与 MRT、Grab 打车、酒店入住、街头小吃点单和紧急求助等落地高频场景整理。"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en-US": "Built for Thailand trips where you move between airports, BTS or MRT lines, ferries, hotels, and food courts in the same day. These cards are most useful when you need a fast request for Grab pickup points, less-spicy food, or simple service help without opening a translator.",
    "zh-CN": "这套泰国短语优先覆盖机场接驳、BTS 或 MRT、码头渡轮、酒店入住和美食广场点餐这些连续切换的场景。遇到要确认 Grab 上车点、说明不要太辣，或者需要快速求助时，直接出示短语卡会比临时翻译更稳。"
  },
  "teaser": {
    "en-US": "Built for Thailand arrivals, BTS transfers, Grab rides, hotel check-ins, and quick street-food conversations.",
    "zh-CN": "适合泰国落地后的 BTS 换乘、Grab 打车、酒店入住和街头点餐沟通。"
  },
  "travelTips": {
    "en-US": [
      "Keep a few basics ready for BTS, MRT, ferry piers, and Grab pickup points because station names and exits move quickly in Bangkok.",
      "Street-food and food-court orders go smoother when you can point to the card first, especially for no spicy, no seafood, or takeaway requests.",
      "Add polite particles like khrap or kha when you can, but showing the phrase on screen is still the fastest option if pronunciation feels uncertain."
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "在曼谷这类节奏很快的城市里，BTS、MRT、码头和 Grab 上车点最好提前备好几句常用短语。",
      "街边摊和美食广场点单时，先给对方看短语卡特别有效，尤其是不要太辣、不要海鲜、打包带走这类需求。",
      "如果发音没把握，加不加 khrap 或 kha 都不是关键，先把短语卡展示出来通常就能顺利沟通。"
    ]
  },
  "highlights": {
    "en-US": [
      "BTS, Grab, and night markets",
      "Street food and spice requests",
      "Hotels, ferries, and airport transfers"
    ],
    "zh-CN": [
      "BTS、Grab 与夜市沟通",
      "街头点餐与辣度需求",
      "酒店、码头与机场接驳"
    ]
  },
  "featured": true,
  "relatedSlugs": [
